PART 2ï¸âƒ£ â€” BASIC EXAMPLE (USER DATA)
1ï¸âƒ£ Create Model + Factory
php artisan make:model User -mf

app/Models/User.php
database/factories/UserFactory.php

2ï¸âƒ£ Use Faker in Factory

 database/factories/UserFactory.php

<?php

namespace Database\Factories;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Factories\Factory;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Hash;

class UserFactory extends Factory
{
    public function definition()
    {
        return [
            'name' => fake()->name(),
            'email' => fake()->unique()->safeEmail(),
            'password' => Hash::make('password'),
            'created_at' => fake()->dateTimeBetween('-1 year'),
        ];
    }
}

PART 3ï¸âƒ£ â€” GENERATE BULK DATA USING SEEDERS
3ï¸âƒ£ Create Seeder
php artisan make:seeder UserSeeder


 database/seeders/UserSeeder.php

<?php

namespace Database\Seeders;

use App\Models\User;
use Illuminate\Database\Seeder;

class UserSeeder extends Seeder
{
    public function run()
    {
        User::factory()->count(1000)->create();
    }
}


âœ” Generates 1000 users

4ï¸âƒ£ Register Seeder

 database/seeders/DatabaseSeeder.php

public function run()
{
    $this->call(UserSeeder::class);
}

5ï¸âƒ£ Run Seeder
php artisan db:seed


Or fresh database:

php artisan migrate:fresh --seed

PART 4ï¸âƒ£ â€” FAKER FOR DIFFERENT DATA TYPES ğŸ”¥
ğŸ”¹ Text & Content
fake()->sentence()
fake()->paragraph()
fake()->text(200)

ğŸ”¹ Numbers & Prices
fake()->numberBetween(100, 1000)
fake()->randomFloat(2, 10, 500)

ğŸ”¹ Dates
fake()->date()
fake()->dateTime()
fake()->dateTimeBetween('-6 months', 'now')

ğŸ”¹ Status / Enum
fake()->randomElement(['active', 'inactive'])

ğŸ”¹ Images (Optional)
fake()->imageUrl(640, 480, 'products')

PART 5ï¸âƒ£ â€” RELATIONAL DATA (VERY IMPORTANT ğŸ”¥)
Example: User has many Posts
Post Factory

ğŸ“„ database/factories/PostFactory.php

use App\Models\User;

return [
    'user_id' => User::factory(),
    'title' => fake()->sentence(6),
    'content' => fake()->paragraph(4),
];

Seeder (Large Dataset)
User::factory()
    ->count(100)
    ->hasPosts(20)
    ->create();

PART 6ï¸âƒ£ â€” FACTORY STATES (CONTROL DATA)
Define State
public function admin()
{
    return $this->state([
        'role' => 'admin',
    ]);
}

Use State
User::factory()->count(10)->admin()->create();
